__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>too repetetive though? surely</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1444833523038158970", "author": "mowcius", "author_handle": "mowcius", "user_id": "222799443890536449", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/222799443890536449/cb67ead0dcf8375d5a198a3b1d573884.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Sunday, November 30, 2025 6:32 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-11-30 6:32 p.m.", "text": "Telemetry and sensors", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Telemetry and sensors</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1464020571498221659", "author": "mrlm", "author_handle": "mrlmuk", "user_id": "772305012402421761", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, January 22, 2026 5:15 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-22 5:15 p.m.", "text": "If put a cavity filter on the SDR and can see all kinds of little signals but nothing which looks like the one mentioned even if I really turn up the gain. (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>If put a cavity filter on the SDR and can see all kinds of little signals but nothing which looks like the one mentioned even if I really turn up the gain.</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Saturday, January 24, 2026 1:51 p.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1464026957439045770", "author": "mrlm", "author_handle": "mrlmuk", "user_id": "772305012402421761", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, January 22, 2026 5:40 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-22 5:40 p.m.", "text": "", "content_html": "", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1443864785962799104/1464026957279793356/image.png?ex=69ebf15a&amp;is=69ea9fda&amp;hm=6961633bd1280bd9fb3acf054e656d1be20e788485d2ef576db905971c502ac6&amp;\"> <img class=chatlog__attachment-media src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1443864785962799104/1464026957279793356/image.png?ex=69ebf15a&amp;is=69ea9fda&amp;hm=6961633bd1280bd9fb3acf054e656d1be20e788485d2ef576db905971c502ac6&amp;\" alt=\"Image attachment\" title=\"Image: image.png (279.37 KB)\" loading=lazy> </a></div>"], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1464383545341378702", "author": "ThePlexus", "author_handle": "ogplexus", "user_id": "387354110548115459", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/387354110548115459/ddc68d5fbb439c8628e89e04c2a655ef.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, January 23, 2026 5:17 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-23 5:17 p.m.", "text": "we figured out ours - its anglian water in the fens - they have all their pumping systems linked via a 868 wan which adheres to the 10% duty cycle per the regs - but also appears to be completely ignoring Tx limits.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>we figured out ours - its anglian water in the fens - they have all their pumping systems linked via a 868 wan which adheres to the 10% duty cycle per the regs - but also appears to be completely ignoring Tx limits.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/2.png alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=mrlmuk>mrlm</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1464027106769113098')\"> I occasionally get this though, only ever seen it twice so not had chance to investigate but if fills the full 10Mhz of the SDR and the cavity filter does nothing to block it. It might be better with IF ACG on . </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1464387695617900565", "author": "mrlm", "author_handle": "mrlmuk", "user_id": "772305012402421761", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, January 23, 2026 5:33 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-23 5:33 p.m.", "text": "I have gonne back to the SDR Play connect software, as its better suited than others and less complicated than SDRuno.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I have gonne back to the SDR Play connect software, as its better suited  than others and less complicated than  SDRuno.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1464392401282924707", "author": "mrlm", "author_handle": "mrlmuk", "user_id": "772305012402421761", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, January 23, 2026 5:52 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-23 5:52 p.m.", "text": "Whatever all that red is, it's in mine or neighboring houses. Looks like electrical interference but the SDR config needs to be tweaked to make any sense of it. (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Whatever all that red is, it&#39;s in mine or neighboring houses. Looks like electrical interference but the SDR config needs to be tweaked to make any sense of it.</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Saturday, January 24, 2026 5:09 p.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/387354110548115459/ddc68d5fbb439c8628e89e04c2a655ef.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=ogplexus>ThePlexus</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1464383545341378702')\"> we figured out ours - its anglian water in the fens - they have all their pumping systems linked via a 868 wan which adheres to the 10% duty cycle per the regs - but also appears to be completely ignoring Tx limits. </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1464529520630562922", "author": "mowcius", "author_handle": "mowcius", "user_id": "222799443890536449", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/222799443890536449/cb67ead0dcf8375d5a198a3b1d573884.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Saturday, January 24, 2026 2:57 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-24 2:57 a.m.", "text": "Make a complaint to Ofcom? (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Make a complaint to Ofcom?</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Saturday, January 24, 2026 2:57 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/387354110548115459/ddc68d5fbb439c8628e89e04c2a655ef.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=ogplexus>ThePlexus</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1464383545341378702')\"> we figured out ours - its anglian water in the fens - they have all their pumping systems linked via a 868 wan which adheres to the 10% duty cycle per the regs - but also appears to be completely ignoring Tx limits. </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}]}